# Figma Plugin Frontend Build

When changing plugin frontend files, make sure the files loaded by Figma are updated before finishing.

- If editing `apps/figma-plugin/dist/ui.html` or `apps/figma-plugin/dist/code.js`, no separate build is needed; remind the user to reopen the plugin.
- If editing `apps/figma-plugin/src/code.ts`, rebuild or manually sync the generated change into `apps/figma-plugin/dist/code.js`.
- If a build script exists, prefer running the project build command after HTML/JS/TS frontend edits.
- After frontend edits, check lints for the changed files.
